{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀποκρίνω</b> [ῑ], <br /> <i>future</i> -κρῐνῶ, <b>set apart,</b> probably in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus “Supp.” 5.7, 5th c.BC: Pherecrates Comicus 23, 2nd-3rd c.AD: Aelianus “Varia Historia” 12.8; χωρὶς ἀ. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Politicus” 302c, +others\">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <b>to be parted or separated,</b> ἀποκρινθέντε <b>parted from the throng</b> (of two πρόμαχοι), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 5.12 (nowhere else in 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus); πίθηκος ᾔει θηρίων ἀποκριθείς 7th c.BC: Archilochus Lyricus 89.3 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of the elements in cosmogony, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Empedocles Poeta Philosophus 9.4, 5th c.BC: Anaxagoras Philosophus 2, 3rd c.AD: Democritus Epigrammaticus 167; ἀπεκρίθη.. τοῦ βαρβάρου ἔθνεος τὸ Ἑλληνικόν 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.60; χωρίς θηρίων ἡ δίαιτα ἀποκέκριται [prev. author] 2.36\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀποκεκρίσθαι εἰς ἓν ὄνομα <b>to be separated and brought</b> under one name, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.3\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; οὐ βεβαίως ἀπεκρίθησαν, of combatants, <b>separated</b> without decisive result, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 4.72. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> in Medicine texts in <i>passive</i>, <b>to be distinctly formed,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “προγνωστικόν” 23 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of the embryo, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 561a17\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; τὰ ἐν τῷ σώματι -όμενα bodily <b>secretions,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἀρχαίης ἰητρικῇς” 14; τὰ ἐς τὴν κοιλίην ἀ. [prev. author] “Vict.” 4.89\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; but ἐς τοῦτο πάντα ἀπεκρίθη all illnesses <b>determined</b> or <b>ended</b> in this <b>alone,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.49; also ᾗ τὰ περιττώματα ἀποκρίνεται \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>are voided,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Partibus Animalium” 665b24, compare “GA” 773b35. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>mark by a distinctive form, distinguish,</b> πρύμνην[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.194; νόσημά τι ἀποκεκριμένον \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>specific,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 407d, compare 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Meteorologica” 369b29. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>choose,</b> ἕνα ὑμῶν ἀ. ἐξαίρετον[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.130\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀ. τοῦ πεζοῦ, τοῦ στρατοῦ, <b>choose from..,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.17, 25\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; δυοῖν ἀποκρίνας κακοῖν <b>having set apart,</b> i.e. <b>decreed,</b> one of two, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 640. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>exclude,</b> πλήθει τῶν ψήφων[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 946a. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>reject on examination,</b> κρίνειν καὶ ἀ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 751d; ἐγκρίνειν καὶ ἀ. [prev. work] 936a\">Refs</a>]; ἀ. τινὰ τῆς νίκης <b>decide</b> that one <b>has lost</b> the victory, <b>decide</b> it <b>against</b> one, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1315b18\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>middle</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 966d. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> <i>middle</i>, ἀποκρίνομαι, <i>future</i> -κρῐνοῦμαι, etc.: [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] uses <i>perfect</i> and <i>pluperfect</i> <i>passive</i> in <i>middle</i> sense, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Prt.” 358a, “Grg.” 463c\">Refs</a>], etc., but also in <i>passive</i> sense (see. below):—<b>give answer to, reply to</b> question,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" uncertain 1. in 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.49, 8.101 (elsewhere ὑποκρ-),compare 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Bacchae” 1271, “IA” 1354; ἀ. τινί 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 1245, etc.: _metaphorically_, ἀ. τοῖς πράγμασιν ὡς ἐπὶ τῶν ἐρωτημάτων 2nd c.AD: Arrianus Historicus “Epicteti Dissertationes” 2.16.2\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀ. πρός τινα, πρὸς τὸ ἐρωτώμενον, <b>to</b> a questioner or question, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 5.42, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 338d; ἀ. εἰ.. 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 964; ἀ. ὅτι.. 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.90: with _accusative_, ἀποκρίνεσθαι τὸ ἐρωτηθέν\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>to answer</b> the question, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 3.61, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Crito” 49a, “Hp.Ma.” 287b, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Metaphysica” 1007a9: with _accusative_ _cognate_, ἀ. οὐδὲ γρῦ 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 17; οὐδὲν ξυμβατικόν 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 8.71; ἀ. ἀπόκρισιν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 658c:\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] —<i>passive</i>, τοῦτό μοι ἀποκεκρίσθω <b>let</b> this <b>be</b> my <b>answer,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Tht.” 187b\">Refs</a>]; καλῶς ἄν σοι ἀπεκέκριτο your <b>answer would have been</b> sufficient, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Grg.” 453d, compare “Men.” 75c, “Euthd.” 299d. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__IV.2</b></Level3> <b>answer charges, defend oneself,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 632; ὁ ἀποκρινόμενος \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>the defendant,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Antipho Orator 6.18, compare 2.4.3\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀπεκρινάμην frequently in legal documents, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PHib.” 1.31.24 (3rd c.BC), etc. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__IV.3</b></Level3> <i>aorist</i> <i>passive</i> ἀπεκρίθη, ={ἀπεκρίνατο}, he <b>answered,</b> condemned by [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Phrynichus Atticista 86\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>], is unknown in earlier <i>Attic dialect</i>, except in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pherecrates Comicus 51, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus Alcaeus2.149b; but occurs in Machoap. 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 8.349d, “UPZ” 6.30 (2nd c.BC), “SIG” 674.61 (Narthacium, 2nd c.BC), “IG” 4.679 (Hermione, 2nd c.BC), 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 4.30.7, etc.; once in 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus, “AJ” 9.3.1, twice in 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista, “Sol.” 5, “Demon.” 26; regular in LXX (but sometimes ἀπεκρινάμην\">LXX+5th c.BC+</a>] in solemn language, as [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “3 Ki.” 2.1)\">Refs</a>] and prevails in “NT” especially in the phrase ἀποκριθεὶς εἶπεν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.Matt.3.15; ἀ. λέγει NT.Mark.8.20, +others, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 2.1.22 codices: \">NT+5th c.BC+</a>]<i>future</i> ἀποκριθήσομαι in same sense, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Isa.14.32, +others, NT.Matt.25.45, 2nd c.AD: Hermogenes Rhetor “περὶ εὑρέσεως” 4.6.\">LXX+NT+2nd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G0611","accentedUnicode":"ἀποκρίνω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0470","matchingForm":"ἀνταποκρίνομαι","stepTransliteration":"antapokrinomai","gloss":"to contradict","_zh_tw_Gloss":"強嘴","_es_Gloss":"contradicer","_zh_Gloss":"强嘴"},{"strongNumber":"G0575","matchingForm":"ἀπό","stepTransliteration":"apo","gloss":"away from","_zh_tw_Gloss":"從","_es_Gloss":"de","_zh_Gloss":"从"},{"strongNumber":"G0610","matchingForm":"ἀπόκριμα","stepTransliteration":"apokrima","gloss":"verdict","_zh_tw_Gloss":"斷定","_es_Gloss":"veredicto","_zh_Gloss":"断定"},{"strongNumber":"G0612","matchingForm":"ἀπόκρισις","stepTransliteration":"apokrisis","gloss":"answer","_zh_tw_Gloss":"應對, 回答","_es_Gloss":"respuesta","_zh_Gloss":"应对, 回答"},{"strongNumber":"G2919","matchingForm":"κρίνω","stepTransliteration":"krinō","gloss":"to judge","_zh_tw_Gloss":"審判","_es_Gloss":"juzgar","_zh_Gloss":"审判"}],"shortDef":"to answer, reply; sometimes used in the NT in the Hebraic sense of continuing a discourse","mediumDef":"to answer, reply; sometimes used in the NT in the Hebraic sense of continuing a discourse <br /><b>to answer, reply</b> <ref='Mat.3.15'>Mt. 3:15</ref>; in NT <b>to respond</b> to certain present circumstances, <b>to avow,</b> <ref='Mat.11.25'>Mt. 11:25</ref>","stepGloss":"to answer","stepTransliteration":"apokrinō","count":247,"_es_Definition":"act. en sig. contestar, replicar ; responder (e.g. MAR.9:5) ; decir, declarar; continuar (un discurso)","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 回答, 回覆<br>2) 繼續 (說)","_zh_Definition":"1) 回答, 回复<br>2) 继续 (说)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"đáp ; luận xét; trong NT theo nghĩa Hy bá lai của việc tiếp tục một bài giảng (Ma 11:25)","_zh_tw_Gloss":"回答","_es_Gloss":"responder","_zh_Gloss":"回答"}]}